@@eThe Cinderteeth Mountains@@N

A discontinuous volcanic arc running west to northeast in broken
tooth-ridges, the Cinderteeth are a recurring civilizational stressor.
Tremors, ash, and route instability force every nearby institution to
reveal what it values when survival grows expensive.

Before the Keepers arrived with survey tablets, the range had permanent
inhabitants: the @@yVentspeakers@@N, a highland people who maintained
interpretive relationships with specific volcanic vents. They read gas
color, tremor rhythm, and vent sound as pronouncements -- practical
geology encoded in ritual vocabulary. Their polished @@dname-stones@@N
still mark vent mouths at elevations few travelers reach.

The @@WSpirebound Conclave@@N built their sanctum in the range's Western
Fold, choosing isolation that made research possible and accountability
impossible. They embedded @@lresonance crystals@@N at fault intersections
throughout the Bellspine ridge, intending to monitor seismic precursors.
When the Conclave collapsed, those anchors were never retrieved. Some
still ring faintly in the deep rock.

The mountains are tectonically coupled to a deep fault running beneath
the continent. Seismic events as far away as the oasis-pyramid corridor
can trigger sympathetic tremors here. This coupling drove the @@rAshfall
catastrophe@@N -- volcanic eruptions that sent ash clouds across the
continent, contaminating wells, poisoning streams, and devastating
@@yKowloon@@N's delta settlement with the Ashfall Monsoon.

Six subregions define the range: the @@rEmber Crown@@N of active calderas
and lethal glassfall, the @@dBellspine@@N where subsurface resonance
disorients travelers, the @@WChalkwind Saddles@@N of commercial transit,
the @@yGlasswash Fans@@N of obsidian quarries and sulfur gardens, the
@@gBlackstep Footholds@@N where mountain law meets civic law, and the
hidden @@lWestern Fold@@N where Conclave ruins still smolder.

Route houses maintain @@yHazard Doctrine@@N -- codified survival protocols
born from disaster. The @@WSilent Bell Protocol@@N demands halt and
dispersal when the mountain's resonance shifts. @@rDouble-water doctrine@@N
forbids mixing hydration reserves after the Ashblind Convoy Loss at
the Dead Pools. These are not superstitions but hard-won law, written
in the names of the dead.

The @@rAsh Cult@@N claims eruptions pronounce divine verdict against civic
corruption -- a degraded echo of Ventspeaker doctrine, stripped of its
empirical rigor and loaded with apocalyptic meaning.
